@startuml
title Use Case 7: Change User Login Info (IT User)

actor ITUser as "User (IT)"
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Server as "Server"
collections Cache as "Server Cache\n(User data)"
collections Store as "Server Persistent Storage\n(User records)"

== Search for user ==
ref over ITUser, GUI, Client, Server, Cache: Searching For A User
ITUser -> GUI: Select User 
GUI --> ITUser: Display Actions Menu 
== Submit change ==
ITUser -> GUI: Choose "Change Login Info"\nEnter new login info\nClick "Submit"
GUI -> Client: SubmitLoginInfoChange(targetUserId,\n newLoginInfo)

Client -> Server: UpdateUserLoginInfo(targetUserId,\n newLoginInfo)


Server -> Store: Write updated login info\nfor target user
Store --> Server: Update stored
Server -> Cache: Update cached user record
Server --> Client: Update OK
Client -> GUI: Show success confirmation
@enduml
